         IFC is considering to provide an A Loan of up to EUR10 million to part-finance the investment plan of Subati Group (Subati or the Company) aimed at expanding and diversifying its high quality rose exports. Subati is undertaking a three-year Project (2016-2018) of US$19.5 million in Kenya comprised of (i) upgrade of existing 80ha rose farms; (ii) development of 15ha new rose farm; and (iii) scale up of fresh herb farm to 40ha with a cold storage facility, water treatment plant, and solar panels.

